(181, 'Operating System', 'Basic', ' What is the main function of the command interpreter?', 'to provide the interface between the API and application program', 'to handle the files in the operating system', 'to get and execute the next user-specified command', 'none of the mentioned', 'No', 'No', 'The main function of a command interpreter is to get and execute the next user-specified command. Command Interpreter checks for valid command and then runs that command else it will throw an error.', 'No', '2021-11-16', 'C', 1),
(182, 'Operating System', 'Basic', 'To access the services of the operating system, the interface is provided by the ___________', ' Library', 'System calls', 'Assembly instructions', 'API', 'No', 'To access services of the Operating System an interface is provided by the System Calls. Generally, these are functions written in C and C++. Open, Close, Read, Write are some of most prominently used system calls.', 'No', 'No', '2021-11-16', 'B', 1),
